texts: GAIAシステム音声
Exiting VR dive mode.
アスマ
Asuma opened his eyes. He was seated in a chair.
Anyone coming out of a VR dive would be fatigued, and Asuma was no exception. He stood up slowly.
Before him, there was the large spherical monitor.
It displayed the Earth—at least, the Earth according to GAIA's simulation.
Asuma looked away from it, spinning his cube-shaped device over and over again.
An exact display of the simulated scenery Asuma had been watching appeared on the control room's monitor.
It showed the intersection between Loop 7 and Koshu-Kaido.
It was the place where, two days ago, a young boy and girl had had an altercation with the army.
アスマ
アスマ
Why? What's going on here?
アスマ
No matter how many times I run the simulation, GAIA's results don't make sense.
アスマ
This never happened before.
アスマ
It can't be real. I mean, how?
アスマ
How can the girl just...not exist?
